{
  "texts": [
    "This further proves that the implicit probability is a better indicator than the explicit probability.",
    "We find that in some cases, while the LLM provides an answer and an explicit probability as instructed, this probability is less than 50% (Supplementary Table 3).",
    "This implies that although the model proposes an answer, it assigns a higher probability to the alternative, undermining its reliability.",
    "In contrast, the implicit probability always selects the most probable token, avoiding such contradictions and supporting its reliability over the explicit probability.",
    "Large LLM vs. small LLM The AUROCs of the large LLMs and their smaller counterparts on the USMLE and MGB-SDoH datasets are shown in Fig. 1."
  ]
}